)\nItems, the activity type, and any categories or axis labels MUST share a single mental model — a participant must be able to act on each item using the structure.\n\n## Fun Activities (icebreakers, warm-ups, casual/fun activities, games)\nThese earn conversation by people EXPLAINING their placements. Each item must REQUIRE a stance — its placement can't be obvious from the item's wording. Pass: 'Pineapple on pizza?' on an Agree/Disagree slider (every answer is a defended stance). Fail: 'Has lived in 3+ places' sorted into a 'Life & Background' column (mechanical; nothing to explain).\n"})}static get values(){return[UcCKk.qZ]}};
