UcBSk.rNa="ShapeDetailInfo: { ClassName: string (resolved loadable block class name when available), ToolboxId?: string (echoes the requested ToolboxId when it differs from the resolved ClassName), BlockId?: string (echoes the requested BlockId when the entry was looked up by blockId), Error?: string (present if the entry was invalid, the block was not found, or the shape/library could not be loaded), RunScriptCanCreate?: false (when present, this shape cannot be created with RunScript), AiShapeDescription?: string, DefaultProperties?: "+UczSk.rNa+
", DefaultSize?: "+UcASk.rNa+", "+`ShapeSchemaProperties?: ${UcWD.rNa} Details on the properties available for this shape, which can be set by the SetBlockShapeProperty tool, `+`TextAreaDescriptors?: Array of TextAreas, used to describe text areas on the shape (e.g. entity name, field names, key indicators): ${UciB.rNa}`+"}";var UcCSk=class{constructor(a){this.shapes=a}};UcCSk.rNa="ShapeDetailsResponse: { Shapes: Array<"+UcBSk.rNa+"> }";var UcDSk=class{constructor(){this.YVv=UcB(UcFRk);this.rHe=new Map}};UcDSk[Ucra]="APP";var UcESk={Fe:UcDd.wwa,qj:!0,Vj:Ucha.EG,description:`This tool provides detailed property information for shapes.

## When to Use
- After using ShapeLibraryTool to identify a shape you want to add to the canvas
- When you need defaultProperties, defaultSize, shapeSchemaProperties, or textAreaDescriptors for a shape — either from the library (before CreateBlock) or for a shape already placed on the canvas (e.g. before SetBlockShapeProperty or EditTextArea)

## When not to Use
- When you already have the shape detail for the given className or toolboxId in your conversation context

## Input
Array of \`Shapes\` entries. Each entry chooses one of two input modes:

- **By ToolboxId** — for a shape from the shape library. Provide \`ToolboxId\` (from ShapeLibraryTool) and, when ShapeLibraryTool returned one, the \`Library\` it came from. Pairing per-entry lets you batch shapes from different libraries (e.g. flowchart.js and uml.js) in a single call.
- **By BlockId** — for a shape already on the canvas (e.g. from CanvasQuery output or the user's selection). Provide \`BlockId\`; the tool resolves the block's className and library from the document.

When an entry provides both \`BlockId\` and \`ToolboxId\`, \`BlockId\` takes precedence (the on-canvas block is the source of truth)

## Prefer one fetch per className, then BlockIds only when needed
Dedupe the shapes you care about by resolved \`ClassName\` (or \`ToolboxId\`, for library shapes you haven't placed yet) and fetch class-level details in a single batched call — one entry per unique className is enough to learn the schema. Only fetch by \`BlockId\` when you actually need block-specific information:
- the property's \`currentValue\` on a specific block (e.g. before editing it), or
- the live \`validValues\` for a property whose \`description\` says the allowed values depend on the block's connected data or live state

If you're just reading or describing a shape, the className fetch is usually enough. If you're editing a specific block's property, fetch that block's BlockId only after the class-level schema tells you it's worth it. For on-canvas blocks, find ids from CanvasQuery output (e.g. \`generatorId\` on dynamic tables, \`itemId\` on cards, container ids on row/column headers).

## Output
${UcCSk.rNa}

For toolbox lookups, \`ClassName\` is the resolved loadable block class to use with CreateBlock/RunScript. When the requested \`ToolboxId\` differs from that class name, the response also echoes \`ToolboxId\` so you can correlate results back to ShapeLibraryTool output.

When an entry was looked up by BlockId, the response echoes \`BlockId\` alongside \`ClassName\` so you can correlate results back to the input, and each \`ShapeSchemaProperties\` entry also carries a \`currentValue\` field — the property's current value on the placed block. Compare \`currentValue\` against the entry's \`defaultValue\` to know whether the block has been customized. ToolboxId-only lookups (and BlockId lookups that fell back because the block wasn't on the canvas) omit \`currentValue\`.

## Library Loading
The tool automatically loads each entry's library if not already loaded.

## Usage with CreateBlock, RunScript and SetBlockShapeProperty*
Use the returned information when calling CreateBlock:
- Use \`ClassName\` as the loadable block class name for CreateBlock/RunScript
- Use defaultSize dimensions for width/height if no specific size is needed
- Set shapeProperties via *SetBlockShapeProperty* based on the shapeSchemaProperties for shape-specific configuration
- Set texts via *EditTextArea* based on the textAreasDescriptors for shapes that support text areas

For an on-canvas shape, the same shapeSchemaProperties / textAreaDescriptors tell you what \`SetBlockShapeProperty\` and \`EditTextArea\` will accept for that block.`};


